%e A396357      \    \    \              /    /
%e A396357       90   60   3---21--36--32   50   .
%e A396357         \    \                  /    .
%e A396357          57   9---27--39--48--46    .
%e A396357            \                       /
%e A396357             69--72--78--81--96--62
%e A396357 .
%e A396357 a(11) = 15 as when a(11) is placed its existing adjacent terms are 6 and 20, and 15 is the smallest unused number that has a common factor with both 6 and 20.
